1
00:01:39,650 --> 00:01:41,990
Mama! Mama!

2
00:01:44,390 --> 00:01:46,290
Minister Perospero...

3
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:48,940
I can't believe it...

4
00:01:49,980 --> 00:01:53,080
Mama's back to normal...

5
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:56,910
Pudding made such an extraordinary cake...

6
00:02:01,710 --> 00:02:06,420
I've never seen her so content. Lick.

7
00:02:09,220 --> 00:02:14,090
Mama! You're our captain!
I need to brief you on the current situation.

8
00:02:14,820 --> 00:02:18,390
First of all, Bege should still be in the area...

9
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:20,700
Lick!

10
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:23,550
I'm so happy...

11
00:02:23,550 --> 00:02:26,100
She's not listening at all...

12
00:02:32,810 --> 00:02:33,530
Is that...?!

13
00:02:35,330 --> 00:02:36,610
Huh? Wait!

14
00:02:39,950 --> 00:02:41,900
Hey, that's not it!

15
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,750
That's not the Straw Hats' ship!

16
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,040
What?!

17
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:53,630
That's the Sun Pirates' ship!

18
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:56,880
No way! It took a direct hit!

19
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:58,220
Did they switch?!

20
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:02,530
In that case, where did the Straw Hats go?!

21
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:09,900
Hurry, Wadatsumi!

22
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,860
Get as far as possible!

23
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,700
Are you sure?

24
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:29,870
This is the legendary ship that Fisher Tiger built!

25
00:03:29,870 --> 00:03:31,210
I'm sure!

26
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:32,750
All right!

27
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:35,630
Hurry up! We don't have time!

28
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,680
Ow, ow, ow!

29
00:03:54,550 --> 00:03:55,940
What?! What?!

30
00:04:04,490 --> 00:04:06,410
He's gonna eat us!

31
00:04:07,470 --> 00:04:09,370
Be patient.

32
00:04:09,370 --> 00:04:11,110
What the?!

33
00:04:11,110 --> 00:04:13,460
Where are we?!

34
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:15,800
We're in Wadatsumi's mouth!

35
00:04:18,710 --> 00:04:20,490
Let's escape!

36
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,230
They're in the water!

37
00:04:30,230 --> 00:04:34,480
I wondered what I saw.
It must have been the Giant Monk's hand!

38
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:37,760
All ships! Come about 180 degrees!

39
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:46,590
I won't let you get away,
you damned fishman!

40
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,770
Hot Sea...

41
00:05:01,110 --> 00:05:02,110
Torpedoes!

42
00:05:21,050 --> 00:05:23,960
It's too hot!

43
00:05:29,890 --> 00:05:32,660
Ow, ow, ow, ow!

44
00:05:32,660 --> 00:05:34,490
There it is! Straw Hat's ship!

45
00:05:34,490 --> 00:05:36,140
Wadakichi!

46
00:05:36,140 --> 00:05:39,360
Fire! Sink Straw Hat's ship!

47
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,830
Just go, you guys!

48
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:51,580
Straw Hat!
I was a bad guy on Fishman Island...

49
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:55,040
I'm sorry!

50
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:07,260
But after that, Boss Jinbe still let me join him...
I-I'm so grateful!

51
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,660
That bastard...

52
00:06:10,660 --> 00:06:12,830
Get out of my way,
you blasted umibozu !

53
00:06:10,660 --> 00:06:12,830
Umibozu: (yokai) monk-like sea spirit

54
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,590
Ouch!

55
00:06:19,430 --> 00:06:20,380
Wadatsumi!

56
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:26,210
Since the boss told us
he wanted to join the Straw Hats,

57
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,410
we all decided!

58
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:37,270
Mama will kill anyone who tries to leave.

59
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,820
So we only have one option...

60
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:47,840
You want us to serve as Captain
Jinbe's shield and die instead?!

61
00:06:48,550 --> 00:06:51,940
We can't all die here!
Someone has to tell the story!

62
00:06:51,940 --> 00:06:53,620
Yeah, you're right.

63
00:06:56,330 --> 00:07:02,000
I won't fault anyone for running away!
Those who follow me should be prepared for anything!

64
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:09,960
We won't let them get in the
way of Jinbe's new beginning!

65
00:07:14,790 --> 00:07:16,890
We all made up our minds!

66
00:07:22,230 --> 00:07:23,780
Get down, Wadatsumi!

67
00:07:35,790 --> 00:07:37,750
Aladine! You guys!

68
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:40,790
Jinbe! Straw Hats!
Get out of here!

69
00:07:56,990 --> 00:08:01,440
We wish you a safe voyage!

70
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:14,330
Let's go, men!

71
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,520
Luffy...

72
00:08:47,070 --> 00:08:52,910
Flooding is a sailing ship's weakness.
Be sure to drain the water quickly...

73
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:58,000
or the ship will be heavy and slow.

74
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:02,680
After that, you should patch up the sails
in order to properly catch the wind

75
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:05,460
and escape as fast as you can!

76
00:09:06,770 --> 00:09:11,000
It'll still take several hours
to escape this territory!

77
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:14,220
What are you saying, Jinbe?!
Why are you telling us this?!

78
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,140
Luffy...

79
00:09:25,330 --> 00:09:28,980
I can't leave them behind!

80
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,580
Okay, I got it!

81
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,000
Then... we'll stay, too!

82
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:48,020
They're guarding the rear to cover you!

83
00:09:50,510 --> 00:09:56,930
If you're cornered by the flagship's fleet now,
escape will be impossible!

84
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:58,880
Please allow me...

85
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,730
to bring up the rear!

86
00:10:06,380 --> 00:10:09,730
We'll pull it off and come back alive!

87
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,700
Don't forget, Jinbe!

88
00:10:37,490 --> 00:10:41,080
I am your captain now!

89
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,620
Jinn-uinely Enraged Cleave!

90
00:10:59,210 --> 00:11:00,940
I won't stop the ship, but...

91
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:06,400
I'll wait for you in Wano!
You better be there!

92
00:11:08,410 --> 00:11:09,240
Luffy!

93
00:11:23,870 --> 00:11:25,670
You have my gratitude!

94
00:11:27,110 --> 00:11:28,050
Jinbe!

95
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:34,220
Don't die no matter what!

96
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:49,230
He's still alive? That Straw Hat brat?

97
00:11:49,230 --> 00:11:52,490
Y-Yes, he's alive for now...

98
00:11:52,490 --> 00:11:57,460
but I just got a report that my siblings 
have him cornered at Cacao Island.

99
00:11:57,460 --> 00:11:59,200
He has nowhere to run!

100
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:03,200
I’m going if he’s still alive.

101
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:06,460
Hurry, Golden Tree Frog!

102
00:12:07,290 --> 00:12:10,440
Prepare yourself, Straw Hat...

103
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:16,030
I'll steal your soul and make some
fearsome homies out of it!

104
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:31,590
We survived...

105
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:36,990
Life isn't all bad.
Let's get away quietly.

106
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:39,530
I'm worried about Germa-rero...

107
00:12:39,530 --> 00:12:40,990
Shut up!

108
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:56,050
Burn!

109
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:58,010
Heat Cross!

110
00:13:14,730 --> 00:13:16,380
Are you okay, Aladine?!

111
00:13:16,380 --> 00:13:18,530
Jinbe! You're returning to us?!

112
00:13:18,530 --> 00:13:22,250
No, I'm still a member
of the Straw Hat crew.

113
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:25,910
I'm just staying behind
to protect my captain!

114
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:29,580
Come on now!

115
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:32,710
You're underestimating us!

116
00:13:33,690 --> 00:13:35,460
That's not it, Brother.

117
00:13:37,180 --> 00:13:38,760
Everyone has to survive...

118
00:13:39,810 --> 00:13:43,010
so you can give me a proper send-off!

119
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:47,320
I know your strength better than anyone!

120
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:51,750
Let's make good use of it to ensure
that the Straw Hats escape!

121
00:14:19,590 --> 00:14:21,260
Those bastards!

122
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:24,810
It's a maelstrom!

123
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:43,620
Brook! Hurry and get the Sunny
as far as you can!

124
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:45,830
Understood!

125
00:14:51,090 --> 00:14:54,290
When fishmen get serious,
we can change the current of the ocean itself!

126
00:14:56,130 --> 00:14:57,130
Amazing!

127
00:14:57,130 --> 00:14:58,050
The sea is...

128
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:08,890
The current that the fishmen generated
is carrying the Sunny away!

129
00:15:10,780 --> 00:15:12,190
Jinbe...

130
00:15:18,290 --> 00:15:22,570
Jinbe is covering Straw Hat Luffy
as he sails away!

131
00:15:22,570 --> 00:15:25,320
Our fleet is completely tied down,

132
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:28,450
and we'll soon lose track of their ship!

133
00:15:31,590 --> 00:15:33,550
That's right! Go, Straw Hat!

134
00:15:33,550 --> 00:15:35,290
Why are you cheering him on?

135
00:15:35,290 --> 00:15:38,860
Ah... that's because Straw Hat
is a prime candidate.

136
00:15:38,860 --> 00:15:39,920
For what?

137
00:15:40,450 --> 00:15:45,760
Stussy... you know about the 
Worst Generation, don't you?

138
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,970
"Surgeon of Death" Trafalgar Law.

139
00:15:51,140 --> 00:15:54,020
Basil Hawkins "The Magician."

140
00:15:55,130 --> 00:15:57,770
"Red Flag" X Drake.

141
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:01,740
"Roar of the Sea" Scratchmen Apoo.

142
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:05,280
Capone "Gang" Bege.

143
00:16:06,460 --> 00:16:09,120
Jewelry Bonney "The Glutton."

144
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:12,540
"Mad Monk" Urouge.

145
00:16:13,710 --> 00:16:16,290
Eustass "Captain" Kid.

146
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:19,960
"Soldier of Slaughter" Killer.

147
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:24,430
Marshall D. "Blackbeard" Teach.

148
00:16:24,430 --> 00:16:25,260
And...

149
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:29,610
"Straw Hat" Monkey D. Luffy.

150
00:16:31,130 --> 00:16:32,860
I'm certain...

151
00:16:33,890 --> 00:16:38,150
that someone from this
so-called Worst Generation...

152
00:16:39,490 --> 00:16:43,070
will rise up and become the next pirate king!

153
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:50,780
I see. So Pedro...

154
00:16:51,650 --> 00:16:53,120
is dead.

155
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:01,420
My name is Pedro! Please help me...

156
00:17:02,110 --> 00:17:06,340
Get them treated now...
or they'll die!

157
00:17:07,430 --> 00:17:09,830
The world needs them!

158
00:17:11,310 --> 00:17:13,310
Those two...

159
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:19,150
can never...

160
00:17:19,150 --> 00:17:21,710
be allowed to die!

161
00:17:27,850 --> 00:17:30,360
It's because he came to rescue me...

162
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:32,540
I don't think this was
where he was supposed to die...

163
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:39,490
It's all right. It's all right, Sanji!

164
00:17:39,490 --> 00:17:41,890
This was Pedro's own choice!

165
00:17:42,530 --> 00:17:45,470
Please don't blame yourself! Sanji!

166
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:52,830
You guys saved the Mokomo Dukedom,
so he wanted to repay the favor!

167
00:17:52,830 --> 00:17:56,570
Besides, if it weren't for Pedro,
we would've all died back there!

168
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:05,700
So...

169
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:14,130
just... thank him.

170
00:18:19,350 --> 00:18:22,750
This is for the best!

171
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:33,420
I know what kind of man he was.

172
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:58,630
♪ Soul Pocus... ♪

173
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:58,630
♪ Soul Pocus... ♪

174
00:18:58,630 --> 00:19:04,340
♪ The soul cries out... ♪

175
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:10,460
♪ with deep doubt ♪

176
00:19:10,460 --> 00:19:16,610
♪ The tide guides the way... pulling the ship away... ♪

177
00:19:16,610 --> 00:19:26,060
♪ from the sea consumed by a fearsome fray! ♪

178
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:36,320
It's a cotton candy flurry!

179
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:41,570
We must be close to the border.

180
00:19:46,490 --> 00:19:50,750
Just a bit further and we'll be 
out of Big Mom's territory!

181
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:57,800
♪ Mama’s back! ♪

182
00:19:58,180 --> 00:19:59,920
♪ Flower! ♪

183
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:06,010
♪ I'm sure they faced great adversity! ♪

184
00:20:06,010 --> 00:20:11,890
♪ Yet the flowers and trees sing brightly! ♪

185
00:20:11,890 --> 00:20:16,090
♪ And they seduce us so sweetly! ♪

186
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:22,320
♪ Soul Pocus! ♪

187
00:20:22,320 --> 00:20:35,520
♪ It's all the plan of our greedy Mama, a grand show for all! ♪

188
00:20:40,140 --> 00:20:43,250
♪ The fairy-tale prince! ♪

189
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:46,510
♪ The beautiful princess! ♪

190
00:20:46,510 --> 00:20:58,440
♪ Shoved into a loveless puppet show! ♪

191
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:10,950
♪ Like a hard heart lured in by a nectar’s sweet smell! ♪

192
00:21:10,950 --> 00:21:22,840
♪ If there's anything in this world
worse than sweetness, it's hard to tell! ♪

193
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:30,070
♪ Hidden motivations and misconceptions... ♪

194
00:21:30,070 --> 00:21:41,440
♪ make you play your role or you'll risk your soul... ♪

195
00:21:49,180 --> 00:21:52,200
♪ Join and get candy! ♪

196
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:55,690
♪ Leave and it’s the guillotine! ♪

197
00:21:55,700 --> 00:22:06,470
♪ Who will win this thrilling fight? ♪

198
00:22:06,470 --> 00:22:10,100
Fishman Karate Secret Technique:

199
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:12,390
Vagabond Drill!

200
00:22:18,810 --> 00:22:20,440
Hang in there!

201
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:24,820
Once Luffy and the others get out
of the territory, we can go too!

202
00:22:35,550 --> 00:22:38,230
Hey, what happened to the Straw Hats?

203
00:22:38,230 --> 00:22:40,420
There's been no word from our pursuit unit!

204
00:22:40,420 --> 00:22:42,880
I think they lost them!

205
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:48,330
Idiot! Once they cross the border,
we won't be able to catch up!

206
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:58,700
Pudding, like usual,
you must seduce him with your acting skills.

207
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:00,690
That's no problem, Mama!

208
00:23:01,330 --> 00:23:04,890
You're like a puppet, Pudding.

209
00:23:04,890 --> 00:23:07,820
Ready to play out my will.

210
00:23:10,570 --> 00:23:14,080
Mama... I'm not a puppet...

211
00:23:16,790 --> 00:23:19,650
Let's get married tomorrow.

212
00:23:19,650 --> 00:23:24,710
Yeah, right... Like all the others,
once he finds out who I really am, he'll...

213
00:23:24,710 --> 00:23:28,260
Even if you're my daughter, 
I can't deny that's creepy...

214
00:23:28,260 --> 00:23:29,260
She's a monster!

215
00:23:30,030 --> 00:23:33,180
"Let's get married!"

216
00:23:31,670 --> 00:23:33,180
You sound exactly like him!

217
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:34,820
So creepy!

218
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:36,770
Look! She's a freak!

219
00:23:36,770 --> 00:23:38,310
Don't do it!

220
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:43,620
No one could ever really love me.

221
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:46,780
I'm just an ugly freak.

222
00:23:47,220 --> 00:23:50,860
Like all the others,
once you find out who I really am...

223
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:56,370
Take a good look, Sanji...
at my creepy...

224
00:23:56,940 --> 00:23:59,040
third eye!

225
00:24:04,550 --> 00:24:07,670
What a beautiful eye!

226
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,090
What?

227
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:17,210
All right! Let's start baking!

228
00:24:21,130 --> 00:24:25,350
I'm glad that you were the one
to play my fiancée, Pudding-chan!

229
00:24:32,110 --> 00:24:33,690
Pudding-chan!

230
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:36,800
H-Hey, Sanji...

231
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,330
...-san...

232
00:24:40,290 --> 00:24:42,250
could you do me a favor?!

233
00:25:39,540 --> 00:25:41,430
Oh...? Pudding-chan?!

234
00:25:42,670 --> 00:25:45,330
You said that you wanted...
to ask me a favor...

235
00:25:45,330 --> 00:25:47,020
What was it?

236
00:26:09,460 --> 00:26:13,880
Brother Peros, come in!
Where's Mama now?!

237
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,000
Damn!

238
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:19,000
Minister Mont d'Or!
We got a call from Cacao Island!

239
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,840
It looks like a territorial sea slug 
reported from the border!

240
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:23,390
It's too late!

241
00:26:23,390 --> 00:26:27,600
It signaled an alert of a passing ship!
The Straw Hats have left the territory!

242
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:33,630
Return to your ships, Germa 66!
Mission accomplished!

243
00:26:36,580 --> 00:26:38,700
Roger!

244
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:39,560
Roger!

245
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:40,850
Roger!

246
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,180
Germa is retreating!

247
00:26:43,180 --> 00:26:44,520
Don't let them go!

248
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:46,150
Catch them!

249
00:26:57,090 --> 00:27:01,340
I never wanted to see my big brother
on his back, defeated.

250
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:07,710
Brûlée.

251
00:27:08,280 --> 00:27:14,130
You fell on your back on purpose, didn't you?
You were on your stomach first.

252
00:27:16,630 --> 00:27:18,970
I wonder...

253
00:27:20,770 --> 00:27:22,810
But Brûlée...

254
00:27:22,810 --> 00:27:28,430
all those stories about how I never lie down...

255
00:27:29,730 --> 00:27:30,860
they're not true.

256
00:27:30,860 --> 00:27:35,470
Yeah, I know.
I've seen you through the mirrors.

257
00:27:39,880 --> 00:27:41,750
You've been playing the role...

258
00:27:42,690 --> 00:27:46,270
of the perfect unbeatable man...

259
00:27:46,270 --> 00:27:48,390
for our sake.

260
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:56,840
Katakuri, if you just hid that mouth,
you'd have friends.

261
00:27:56,840 --> 00:28:00,770
Don't want 'em! I am who I am!
I'll just beat up anyone that laughs!

262
00:28:00,770 --> 00:28:02,440
A pelican eel!

263
00:28:03,900 --> 00:28:06,200
He's a pelican eel!

264
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:09,700
I'll kick their asses!

265
00:28:20,650 --> 00:28:21,430
Oh, no!

266
00:28:21,430 --> 00:28:22,920
Hurry!

267
00:28:21,860 --> 00:28:22,940
How could this happen?

268
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:24,110
What is it?

269
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:27,000
What's the matter?

270
00:28:29,630 --> 00:28:30,550
What?!

271
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:29,630
This is serious!
Brûlée is badly injured!

272
00:28:30,550 --> 00:28:31,510
Brûlée!

273
00:28:33,900 --> 00:28:36,350
What... happened?

274
00:28:37,690 --> 00:28:39,480
It's nothing...

275
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:43,810
No, it's not nothing! Tell me!
What happened?!

276
00:28:43,810 --> 00:28:47,860
Those guys you beat up earlier
came back for revenge, Katakuri!

277
00:28:48,190 --> 00:28:50,570
Revenge?! On my sister?!

278
00:28:50,570 --> 00:28:54,130
Why?! Why did she have to be the one to get hurt?!

279
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,520
Big Brother...

280
00:29:02,100 --> 00:29:06,000
It doesn't... hurt at all...

281
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:09,710
You're fine just the way you are, Big Brother.

282
00:29:12,750 --> 00:29:15,160
You fool! I'm...

283
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:20,700
Brûlée got hurt because of me...

284
00:29:24,430 --> 00:29:26,240
I was too naive!

285
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:28,570
Here comes Katakuri!

286
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:30,900
We've been expecting you.

287
00:29:30,900 --> 00:29:33,570
Huh? What's that around your neck?!

288
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:38,580
How dare you scar my sister's face?!

289
00:29:38,580 --> 00:29:41,200
I'll never lower my guard again!

290
00:29:44,570 --> 00:29:48,760
I'll teach you all what true fear is!

291
00:29:51,730 --> 00:29:54,100
Brûlée...

292
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:54,100
Hm?

293
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:55,590
How's Straw Hat?

294
00:29:58,470 --> 00:30:01,430
I'm sure you'll think
"That's a relief" when you hear.

295
00:30:02,450 --> 00:30:05,330
Can you see the future, too?

296
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:10,840
He just made it out of our territory.

297
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:12,760
But I won't forgive him...

298
00:30:12,760 --> 00:30:16,510
after what he put my big brother through!

299
00:30:17,740 --> 00:30:18,980
I knew it.

300
00:30:21,990 --> 00:30:25,620
Luffy and the others made it out of the territory.
Let's retreat!

301
00:30:29,050 --> 00:30:32,260
Germa 66, withdraw!

302
00:30:32,260 --> 00:30:35,780
Fire! Fire! Fire!
Don’t let Germa get away!

303
00:30:42,970 --> 00:30:44,430
Here she comes...

304
00:30:54,150 --> 00:30:55,780
It's Mama!

305
00:31:01,620 --> 00:31:08,100
♪ Soul Pocus! ♪

306
00:31:04,500 --> 00:31:08,100
♪ Soul Pocus! ♪

307
00:31:08,100 --> 00:31:14,310
♪ The selfish excuses you make... ♪

308
00:31:14,310 --> 00:31:20,360
♪ are useless when you’re tempted by a sweet cake! ♪

309
00:31:20,360 --> 00:31:28,120
♪ You should've accounted for what they’d take! ♪

310
00:31:29,590 --> 00:31:41,670
♪ There is nothing to gain! ♪

311
00:31:41,670 --> 00:31:53,690
♪ Give up a treat or be tricked in vain! ♪

312
00:31:53,690 --> 00:32:06,870
♪ Is there anything in this world worse than sweetness' pain? ♪

313
00:32:10,690 --> 00:32:14,670
♪ The Soul Pocus... ♪

314
00:32:14,670 --> 00:32:17,750
♪ of our selfish... ♪

315
00:32:17,750 --> 00:32:25,840
♪ Mama! ♪

316
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:29,010
♪ Will you give up your vitality... ♪

317
00:32:29,010 --> 00:32:33,400
♪ ...or become another fatality? ♪

318
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:37,210
♪ Soul Pocus! ♪

319
00:32:37,210 --> 00:32:40,190
♪ It's our queen's... ♪

320
00:32:40,190 --> 00:32:46,550
♪ song! ♪

321
00:32:46,970 --> 00:32:50,490
Life or death?

322
00:32:53,530 --> 00:33:01,050
Shielded by the efforts of the Sun Pirates, Germa 66,
and those who sacrificed everything,

323
00:33:01,050 --> 00:33:07,930
the Straw Hat crew finally escaped
Emperor Big Mom's territory.

324
00:33:13,060 --> 00:33:14,380
Hey...

325
00:33:15,620 --> 00:33:18,270
Should I prepare a meal?

326
00:33:18,930 --> 00:33:20,490
A meal?

327
00:33:22,610 --> 00:33:24,070
Food!

328
00:33:24,070 --> 00:33:25,840
Sanji's cooking!

329
00:33:25,840 --> 00:33:28,160
I'm actually famished!

330
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:30,950
I'm starving!

331
00:33:30,950 --> 00:33:33,680
It's safe, free, and delicious!

332
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:36,080
Sanji's cooking!

333
00:33:36,610 --> 00:33:40,630
Did something happen while I was gone?

334
00:33:41,570 --> 00:33:44,890
Meanwhile, in the East Blue...

335
00:33:45,630 --> 00:33:47,210
Isn't my meal ready yet?!

336
00:33:47,210 --> 00:33:48,710
Hey, come on!

337
00:33:48,710 --> 00:33:51,300
Owner Zeff! Let's just kick them out!

338
00:33:51,300 --> 00:33:53,180
Why do we have to serve them?

339
00:33:53,180 --> 00:33:55,060
They're criminals!

340
00:33:55,060 --> 00:33:57,980
I'll cook, so just be quiet!

341
00:33:57,980 --> 00:33:59,970
Hurry up and bring the food!

342
00:33:59,970 --> 00:34:01,980
They're pushing their luck!

343
00:34:01,980 --> 00:34:06,240
Food! Food! Food! Food!

344
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:08,070
Okay, okay.

345
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:11,700
No matter the time of day,
everyone still gets hungry.

346
00:34:13,690 --> 00:34:17,120
No matter who they might be, everyone still gets hungry.

347
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,500
Now, dig in!

348
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:22,610
– I'll feed anyone who is hungry!
– I'll feed anyone who is hungry!

349
00:34:22,610 --> 00:34:24,960
– We can talk later!
– We can talk later!

